# Kaappi Book Project

A XeLaTeX book teaching the Kaappi Scheme programming language to beginners who already know Python.

## Build

- Full build: `make` (3 XeLaTeX passes for TOC/index)
- Quick iteration: `make once` (single pass)
- View result: `make view` (opens `build/kaappi-book.pdf`)
- Clean: `make clean`
- Engine: XeLaTeX only (required by fontspec)

## Project Layout

```
main.tex              Document root (title page, preface, \input chapter files)
preamble/
  colors.tex          Color definitions (grayscale palette, darkbrown accent)
  packages.tex        All \usepackage calls (microtype, enumitem, listings, hyperref, etc.)
  fonts.tex           fontspec config: EB Garamond (body), Source Sans 3 (headings), Fira Code (mono)
  fonts-memoir.tex    Memoir heading font overrides
  decorations.tex     Lambda ornament, section/chapter break rules
  layout.tex          6x9" page geometry, margins, chapter style, page style, typography tuning
  styles.tex          Custom mdframed environments (note, warning, exercise, codeoutput)
  listings.tex        Scheme language definition, lstlisting styles (scheme, repl), \code{} macro
chapters/             One .tex file per chapter, \input'd from main.tex
fonts/                Bundled .ttf files (EB Garamond, Source Sans 3, Fira Code)
build/                Output directory (gitignored)
```

## Writing Guidelines

- Target audience: programmers who know Python/JS/Ruby but not Scheme or Lisp
- Use active voice, short sentences, no academic jargon
- Introduce one concept at a time; build on previous chapters
- Every concept must have a runnable Kaappi code example
- Compare to Python equivalents when it clarifies (e.g., "like Python's list comprehension")
- Keep code examples under 20 lines; split longer demos into steps
- Exercises go at the end of chapters inside `\begin{exercise}...\end{exercise}`

## LaTeX Conventions

- Never add \usepackage in chapter files; edit `preamble/packages.tex`
- Never use \lstset in chapter files; global config lives in `preamble/listings.tex`
- Scheme code blocks:
  ```latex
  \begin{lstlisting}
  (define (factorial n)
    (if (= n 0) 1 (* n (factorial (- n 1)))))
  \end{lstlisting}
  ```
- REPL sessions (shows > prompt):
  ```latex
  \begin{lstlisting}[style=repl]
  > (+ 1 2)
  3
  > (string-append "hello" " " "world")
  "hello world"
  \end{lstlisting}
  ```
- Inline code: `\code{define}` or `\lstinline{(+ 1 2)}`
- Informational callout: `\begin{note}[Title]...\end{note}`
- Pitfall/danger: `\begin{warning}[Title]...\end{warning}`
- Practice problems: `\begin{exercise}[Title]...\end{exercise}` (auto-numbered per chapter)
- REPL output display: `\begin{codeoutput}[Title]...\end{codeoutput}`
- Section transition: `\sectionbreak`
- Chapter ending ornament: `\chapterend`
- Cross-references: use `\label{sec:topic}` and `\ref{sec:topic}`
- Index entries: `\index{continuations}` near first significant mention

## Kaappi Reference Sources

When writing about Kaappi features, consult these authoritative sources:

- **Source code**: `/Users/bmuthuka/kaappi/kaappi` (Zig implementation, ~39k LOC)
  - `src/` — core runtime (reader, compiler, VM, GC, primitives, REPL)
  - `lib/` — portable Scheme SRFI libraries (.sld files)
  - `docs/dev/` — architecture, IR, LLVM backend docs
  - `CONFORMANCE.md` — R7RS compliance details
- **Website docs**: `/Users/bmuthuka/kaappi/kaappi.github.io`
  - `docs/guide/tutorial.md` — beginner tutorial (12 sections)
  - `docs/guide/language.md` — language quick reference with examples
  - `docs/procedures/` — 600+ procedure reference by category
  - `docs/guide/srfi-support.md` — SRFI availability table
  - `docs/guide/cli.md` — CLI flags and subcommands
  - `docs/cookbook/` — practical recipes (REST API, JSON, testing, CLI tools)

## Key Kaappi Facts

- R7RS-small compliant (1,391 tests pass), 554 built-in procedures, 33 syntax forms
- 72 SRFIs (8 built-in in Zig, 64 portable Scheme)
- Written in Zig 0.16+; runs on macOS ARM64, Linux x86_64/ARM64/RISC-V, WASM
- Compilation pipeline: Reader → Expander → IR → Bytecode → Register VM (+ optional LLVM native)
- Generational mark-and-sweep GC
- C FFI via `(kaappi ffi)`: ffi-open, ffi-fn, ffi-callback
- Green threads via `(kaappi fibers)`: spawn, yield, channels
- SRFI-18 OS threads (experimental)
- Package manager: thottam
- Install: `curl -fsSL https://kaappi-lang.org/install.sh | bash`
